: {'content': '.'}}, {'type': 'text', 'text': {'content': 'To continue getting these emails, please add james@jamesclear.com to your address book or safelist us.'}}, {'type': 'text', 'text': {'content': '.'}}, {'type': 'text', 'text': {'content': ' This will also remove you from any promotional emails for the book.'}}, {'type': 'text', 'text': {'content': ' '}}, {'type': 'text', 'text': {'content': '\u200b'}}, {'type': 'text', 'text': {'content': ''}}, {'type': 'text', 'text': {'content': ' '}}]}}, {'object': 'block', 'type': 'bulleted_list_item', 'bulleted_list_item': {'text': [{'type': 'text', 'text': {'content': '\u200b'}}, {'type': 'text', 'text': {'content': ' '}}, {'type': 'text', 'text': {'content': ''}}, {'type': 'text', 'text': {'content': 'The most important decision you will make is what habit to build. '}}, {'type': 'text', 'text': {'content': 'Pick the right habit and progress is easy. Pick the wrong habit and life is a struggle. It is much more important to work on the right habit than it is to work really hard. (Working hard is still important, of course.) '}}, {'type': 'text', 'text': {'content': 'In this lesson, we’re going to discuss how to choose the right habit for you.'}}, {'type': 'text', 'text': {'content': 'When most people think about the habits they want to build, they naturally start by considering the outcomes they want to achieve. "I want to lose weight." Or, "I want to stop smoking."'}}, {'type': 'text', 'text': {'content': '.)'}}, {'type': 'text', 'text': {'content': "Here's the short version:"}}, {'type': 'text', 'text': {'content': 'Anyone can convince themselves to practice yoga or meditation once or twice, but if you don’t shift the belief behind the behavior, then it becomes hard to stick with long-term changes. Improvements are only temporary until they become part of who you are.'}}, {'type': 'text', 'text': {'content': 'The goal is not to get straight A’s, the goal is to become a person who studies every day. '}}, {'type': 'tex