out your desired identity and ask, “Who is the type of person that could get the outcome I want?”'}}, {'type': 'text', 'text': {'content': 'What would a healthy person do? What would a productive person do? What would X do? These questions help reveal the desired identity you should be working toward and the habits that support that identity. This is the way to determine which habit you should focus on. '}}, {'type': 'text', 'text': {'content': 'Once you have a handle on the type of person you want to be, you can begin taking small steps to reinforce your desired identity.'}}, {'type': 'text', 'text': {'content': 'Here are some more examples of linking your habits to your desired identity:'}}, {'type': 'text', 'text': {'content': 'If you want to write a book, you should focus on becoming the type of person who writes every day.'}}, {'type': 'text', 'text': {'content': 'If you want to learn a new language, you should focus on becoming the type of person who studies every day.'}}, {'type': 'text', 'text': {'content': 'If you want to retire early, you should focus on becoming the type of person who saves money every month.'}}, {'type': 'text', 'text': {'content': 'The focus should always be on becoming that type of person, not getting a particular outcome. In the beginning, it is far more important to cast small votes for your desired identity than to worry about a particular result.'}}, {'type': 'text', 'text': {'content': "Your habits reshape your identity in a gradual way. It's slow and nearly impossible to see. You can rarely tell a difference between who you were yesterday and who you are today. But with each rep, with each vote cast, your internal story begins to shift. "}}, {'type': 'text', 'text': {'content': 'Start by focusing on who you want to become, not what you want to achieve.'}}, {'type': 'text', 'text': {'content': '\u200b'}}, {'type': 'text', 'text': {'content': "That's all for Lesson 1. See you in the next lesson,"}}, {'type': 'text', 'text': {'conte